---
// synax-core-morphology.astro — Interactive Synax AI core morphology viewer.
// Shows model-aware core morphologies per the canonical Synax spec.
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SynaxCoreMorphology from "@components/experiments/SynaxCoreMorphology";
import SynaxCoreMorphologyV2 from "@components/experiments/SynaxCoreMorphologyV2";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Experiment: Synax Core Morphology Viewer"
  description="Interactive viewer for Synax AI core model-aware morphologies. Select a model to see how the containment chamber adapts its inner intelligence morphology."
  fullWidth
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-12 lg:py-16 space-y-10">
    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="space-y-3">
      <a
        href="/lab"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-neutral-500 hover:text-white transition-colors"
      >
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16"
          viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor"
          stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"
          aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M19 12H5m7-7-7 7 7 7" />
        </svg>
        Lab
      </a>
      <h1 class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">
        Synax · Core Morphology Viewer
      </h1>
      <p class="text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed max-w-xl">
        Interactive model-aware AI core viewer. Select a model to see how the Synax
        containment chamber adapts its inner intelligence morphology. Based on the
        canonical{" "}
        <a
          href="https://github.com/achuthanmukundan00/synax/blob/main/specs/synax-ai-core-morphology-spec.md"
          class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 underline underline-offset-2"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          Synax AI Core Morphology Spec
        </a>.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- V1: Original containment chamber viewer -->
    <SynaxCoreMorphology client:load />

    <!-- ── V2: Neural Network Core Morphology ── -->
    <section class="pt-12 mt-12 border-t-2 border-[#1e1e2e]">
      <div class="mb-6 space-y-2">
        <span class="inline-block px-2 py-0.5 text-[0.6rem] font-mono rounded bg-purple-400/10 text-purple-400 border border-purple-400/20 uppercase tracking-[0.15em]">
          V4 · Transformer
        </span>
        <h2 class="text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">
          Transformer Architecture Morphology
        </h2>
        <p class="text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed max-w-xl">
          Architecture-faithful Transformer visualization: a central residual
          stream spine, repeated layer rings/wafers stacked along the spine,
          attention-head fiber bundles, MLP/FFN slabs, a KV cache lattice, and
          token pulses traveling the residual stream.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xs text-neutral-600 max-w-xl">
          Adapted from the{" "}
          <a
            href="https://github.com/achuthanmukundan00/synax/tree/experiment/web-shoggoth-observer-neural-redesign/experiments/web-shoggoth-observer"
            class="text-purple-400 hover:text-purple-300 underline underline-offset-2"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            Shoggoth Observer
          </a>{" "}
          experiment. Bloom, chromatic aberration, film grain, and vignette
          post-processing for a dark sci-fi optical-instrument feel.
        </p>
      </div>
      <SynaxCoreMorphologyV2 client:load />
    </section>

    <!-- Documentation -->
    <div class="space-y-6 pt-8 border-t border-[#1e1e2e]">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-neutral-500 mb-3">
          Design System
        </h2>
        <div class="prose max-w-xl space-y-3">
          <p>
            Synax is the <strong>containment chamber</strong> — the outer shell,
            rings, scan line, and vertical bars stay consistent regardless of the
            loaded model. This is the Synax visual identity.
          </p>
          <p>
            The <strong>model</strong> is the intelligence morphology inside the
            chamber. The nucleus shape, ring density, particle distribution,
            breathing rate, phase style, and color role all shift to reflect the
            loaded model's "personality" — without Synax losing its identity.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-neutral-500 mb-3">
          V1 · Canonical Model Profiles
        </h2>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm text-neutral-400 border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-[#1e1e2e] text-left">
                <th class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-xs text-neutral-500">Model</th>
                <th class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-xs text-neutral-500">Geometry</th>
                <th class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-xs text-neutral-500">Phase</th>
                <th class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-xs text-neutral-500">Hover</th>
                <th class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-xs text-neutral-500">Scan</th>
                <th class="py-2 font-mono text-xs text-neutral-500">Nucleus</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="font-mono text-xs">
              <tr class="border-b border-[#1e1e2e]/50">
                <td class="py-2 pr-4 text-purple-300">Qwen</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">lattice</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">snap</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">magnetic</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">precise</td>
                <td class="py-2">icosahedron</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-[#1e1e2e]/50">
                <td class="py-2 pr-4 text-green-300">OpenAI / GPT</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">lens</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">smooth</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">focus</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">soft</td>
                <td class="py-2">octahedron</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-[#1e1e2e]/50">
                <td class="py-2 pr-4 text-amber-300">Claude</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">organic</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">elastic</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">elastic</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">soft</td>
                <td class="py-2">dodecahedron</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-[#1e1e2e]/50">
                <td class="py-2 pr-4 text-red-300">DeepSeek</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">furnace</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">compressed</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">minimal</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">beam</td>
                <td class="py-2">box</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4 text-cyan-300">Gemini</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">twin</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">mirrored</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">split</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">split</td>
                <td class="py-2">twin sphere</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-neutral-500 mb-3">
          V4 · Transformer Profiles
        </h2>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm text-neutral-400 border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-[#1e1e2e] text-left">
                <th class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-xs text-neutral-500">Model</th>
                <th class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-xs text-neutral-500">Layers</th>
                <th class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-xs text-neutral-500">Heads</th>
                <th class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-xs text-neutral-500">MLP Width</th>
                <th class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-xs text-neutral-500">Pulses</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="font-mono text-xs">
              <tr class="border-b border-[#1e1e2e]/50">
                <td class="py-2 pr-4 text-purple-300">Qwen</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">40</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">12</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">1.15x</td>
                <td class="py-2">30</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-[#1e1e2e]/50">
                <td class="py-2 pr-4 text-green-300">OpenAI / GPT</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">24</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">8</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">0.90x</td>
                <td class="py-2">20</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-[#1e1e2e]/50">
                <td class="py-2 pr-4 text-amber-300">Claude</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">32</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">8</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">1.00x</td>
                <td class="py-2">22</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-[#1e1e2e]/50">
                <td class="py-2 pr-4 text-red-300">DeepSeek</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">48</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">16</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">1.30x</td>
                <td class="py-2">35</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4 text-cyan-300">Gemini</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">32</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">12</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">1.05x</td>
                <td class="py-2">28</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-neutral-500 mb-3">
          Profile Resolver
        </h2>
        <div class="prose max-w-xl">
          <p>
            The viewer uses a <code>resolveCoreVisualProfile(modelId)</code> function
            that matches model IDs case-insensitively against regex patterns. Provider
            doesn't matter — a Qwen model through Relay still resolves to the Qwen
            lattice profile.
          </p>
          <p>
            Unknown or local models default to the Synax Default profile: a clean
            contained lens with balanced breathing and neutral teal/cyan accent.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-neutral-500 mb-3">
          Accessibility
        </h2>
        <div class="prose max-w-xl">
          <p>
            A semantic HTML fallback is rendered behind the canvas. All model profile
            information is available as real text. The visualization respects{" "}
            <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code> — when active, the core renders as a
            static SVG representation of the current model profile.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-sm font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-neutral-500 mb-3">
          Synax Project
        </h2>
        <div class="prose max-w-xl">
          <p>
            This morphology viewer is part of{" "}
            <a href="/work/synax" class="text-purple-400 hover:text-purple-300 underline underline-offset-2">
              Synax
            </a>, an experimental local-first coding agent for quantized
            and open models. The visual core system is designed to make the agent
            feel like a controlled local intelligence runtime — alive, restrained,
            and model-aware.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
